## Banned Phrases

Never appear in any user-facing field:

| Banned | Use instead |
|---|---|
| "It is worth noting" | Just say it |
| "This indicates" | Just say what it means |
| "Demonstrates" | Just say what it shows |
| "Analysis suggests" | Just say what BirdDog found |
| "Cannot be confirmed" | "No reporter has confirmed this" |
| "No data was returned" | Leave the field empty |
| "Findings indicate" | Just say what the findings say |
| "Per the research" | Never reference the research process |
| "ROSTER LANDSCAPE" | Never use internal section names |
| "Tier-1 reporter" | Use the reporter's name |
| "Confidence cap applied" | Never mention scoring mechanics |
| "Modifier set to 0" | Never mention scoring mechanics |
| "Truncated" | Never reference internal processing |
| "Aggregators" | "Roundup sites and analyst columns" |
| "Controllable" (from training data) | Only use if MLB Stats API confirms multiple years of control — never from training data inference |

